title: For Sale/Trade:  Beautiful M14 for sale/partial trades considered
postcontent:
For your consideration…No expense was spared in the building of this heirloom quality M14. The pics don't do this rifle justice...it's stunning. The barreled receiver is from James River Armory and features a forged receiver and bolt with a Criterion barrel.  The receiver is marked “Rockola M14” (as a tribute to the Rockola company that built Garands during WWII) The build was completed with 100% USGI op rod, trigger group, gas puck, and a beautiful figured birch stock, which was tastefully refinished to retain the history, proof mark and defense stamp (the grain on the grip is darker from being held by soldiers in the past…and that history has been retained). Springfield M1As are quality replicas of M14s, but they are made with investment castings to keep down cost and are not USGI spec. This is a true M14 built to 100% USGI specs. The trigger has been trued and polished, and breaks like glass at 4lbs 10oz (to remain legal for Camp Perry matches).  The sling is a 1903 leather adjustable swivel with brass hardware. The case is padded M1950 paratrooper’s case. Also comes with 3 USGI military issue 20 rd mags…2 still sealed in packaging (these are the best mags you can get…not cheap copies). The scope is a vortex 4-16X50 mounted on med height rings so the iron sights can still be used. This set up shoots 1MOA with match grade ammo. This is an awesome old-school tactical long range set up…sure there are lighter, more accurate modern rifles out there…but this has a cool factor that is unmatched. Cash value $1900. Do your research...It would cost @$2800 to reproduce this set-up
Will take partial trade with cash thrown in to even out the deal

Like th P415, the P308 features all of their Gen4 upgrades such as E2 Extraction Technology, ambidextrous fire controls, modular free floating rail platform, anti-tilit buffer tube, anti-tilt buffer tube, their M-LOK compatible M Rail, and more. The P308 is your best option for certainty in an uncertain world. Specifications:  Caliber: 7.62x51mm Nato Barrel: 16.5" (1:10) Rail Length: 11.5" M-Rail Weight: 8.1lbs-8.5lbs Length: 34"-39.5" (collapsed) Trigger: Standard Drop-IN 4.5lb  Proprietary Technology & Features:  Gen4 Lower Receiver E2 Dual-Extraction Technology: POF's patented E2 dual-extraction technology consists of four small channels cut into the walls of the chamber allowing a small amount of gas pressure to push against the neck of the spent case. This pressure assists in extraction by breaking the seal between the chamber and case as well as pushing the spent case to the rear as the extractor is pulling to the rear. This removes a tremendous amount of work that would otherwise be left up to the extractor. Nitride Heat-Treated Barrel: Proper gas regulation and lubricated mechanics are nothing without the precision and durability of a quality barrel. POF's chrome alloy barrels are machined for absolute accuracy. POF's barrels are nitride heat-treated for full corrosion resistance. Triple Port Muzzle Brake: Designed to precisely compliment the POF platform their nitride heat-treated muzzle brake controls gas dispersion and reduces muzzle rise. It is effective in allowing the shooter to have faster follow up shots and has unbelievably soft felt recoil. It features blunt strike prongs and includes their nitride heat-treated collar jam nut. Oversized Heat Sink Barrel Nut: The patented oversized heat sink barrel nut is one of the most significant innovations. At three inches long it completely emcompasses the bahmber and throat area of the barrel where expanding gas temperatures peak. Take into account the radiation properties of aluminum compared to traditional steel and you have 17 times more heat dissipation than a standard AR. POF's barrel nut's 3" length also gives the operating rod substantial guiding surface assuring constant positive contact with the bolt carrier. POF's enhanced backbone receiver also move the upper's natural stress point forward. This adds a massive amount of rigidity to the overall platform and is critical when vertical fore grips are being pulled on the upper assembly. Bolt Carrier Group: POF's one piece NP3 plated bolt carrier is manufactured with the mechanical key built into the body and positioned behind the cam pin. This patented design helps reduce carrier tilt. POF's bolt carrier group features a chrome plated bolt, extractor, and firing pin. The finishes are both corrosion resistant and introduce lubricious characteristics to the action. Roller Cam Pin: POF's patented roller cam pin is just one more-example of how they strive to reduce friction and drag in the action. Standard AR cam pins feature a square steel head that literally grinds and carves away at the inside of the receiver. POF's NP3 coated roller head actually rolls inside the channel of the upper thus eliminating friction and prolonging the life of the upper. Anti-Tile Buffer Tube: POF's mil-spec aluminum anti-tilt buffer tube features "carrier cradle" extensions to ensure that the carrier is always supported by the buffer tube even when the bolt carrier is fully forward. This prevents carrier tilt and premature wear of the buffer tube. The buffer detent now doubles as a lock that inhibits the buffer tube from rotating and becoming loose under adverse conditions. The anti-tilt buffer tube also features three drain holes. Adjustable Gas System: The POF adjustable gas system consists of three major components, the gas plug, gas piston and operating rod. Residual gasses behind the bullet are routed into the gas block which drives both the piston and the op rod rearward in turn cycling the firearm. Suppressors add back pressure to a firearms operating system and thus increase bolt speed. This causes premature wear on the firearm and can even result in the bolt catching the discharged casing also known as "stove piping". The POF gas system allows the user to restrict, and even shut off, this extra back pressure by simply rotating the gas plug. Modular Railed Receiver: The patented Modular Railed Receiver (M.R.R) is POF's crown jewel for precision and extreme rigidity. This is a two piece upper assembly with a free-floating monolithic handguard that slides on and interfaces directly to the upper assembly tanks to their upper's reinforced backbone. This backbone is five-times thicker than standard flattop platforms. The suspended handguard keeps your grip and accessories from weighing on the barrel and with the help of their wedge block, reduces stress and flex in the barrel extension area. This ensures both extreme rigidity and accuracy by directing stress risers toward the upper assembly's strongest, most reinforced materials.
